    <node id="1. The Conservative party is demanding that the government become a &quot;reliable partner&quot; for the Government of Ontario and the private sector to deliver rural Internet infrastructure to rural Canadians. They want the government to be more serious about addressing the digital divide between urban and rural areas.&#10;2. They are also asking for specific results or a plan from the government regarding when rural municipalities across Canada, including places like Saint-Onsime-d'Ixworth in the riding of Mr. Bernard Gnreux, can have access to reliable high-speed Internet service.&#10;3. Lastly, they are drawing attention to the deplorable state of rural Internet service in Parry Sound-Muskoka, where families and small businesses face issues with affordability, reliability, and availability. They want the government to work on improving this situation by being a reliable partner in northern Ontario broadband projects." />
