    <node id="The Prime Minister, Justin Trudeau, is being accused of acting like a monarch with a divine right because of his behavior regarding the extension of the Special Committee on the COVID-19 Pandemic's mandate. Despite receiving a minority mandate from Quebecers and Canadians, he has acted as if he has the authority of a majority government, disregarding the opposition's proposal to extend the committee's mandate and help people with disabilities.&#10;&#10;The Bloc Québécois proposed to split the government's bill in two to assist people with disabilities and extend the discussions on this matter. However, Trudeau refused this assistance, stating that unanimous consent of the Chamber was required to debate it, and the Conservative Party voted against it. This has led to accusations that he is not respecting the voice of the majority in Parliament and acting as if he has a divine right to rule.&#10;&#10;Furthermore, Trudeau's refusal to provide a fiscal update during the COVID-19 pandemic has added to the perception that he is trying to sideline Parliament, dominate the news cycle, and keep everyone in the dark about the state of the economy. This has led to calls for transparency and accountability from the opposition parties, who argue that Canadians deserve to understand the current state of the economy." />
