    <node id="1. The Liberal government, led by Prime Minister Justin Trudeau, has not yet committed to a review of the RCMP budget with the specific intention of reallocating resources to community services and addressing systemic racism, as requested by Black Lives Matter and other advocates.&#10;2. Despite acknowledging the presence of systemic racism within the criminal justice system, including the RCMP, and recognizing the need for equitable outcomes for Indigenous people, black Canadians, and other racialized people, the Liberal government has not taken any concrete steps to implement reforms or an action plan related to the National Inquiry into Missing and Murdered Indigenous Women and Girls.&#10;3. The city of Montreal has recognized systemic racism and announced measures to address it, contrasting with the Liberal government's approach towards reforming the RCMP and dealing with systemic racism.&#10;4. While the Liberal government claims a commitment to addressing systemic racism in Canada, their lack of action on implementing reforms or the action plan for the National Inquiry into Missing and Murdered Indigenous Women and Girls, along with not allocating resources towards community services instead of policing, contradicts these statements." />
