    <edge source=" I am asking questions for Canadians. Why are the government and the Minister of Finance, Bill Morneau, not able to table an economic update when some provinces are able to?&#10;Speaker: Hon. Mona Fortier&#10;Content: Once again, I would like to remind my hon. colleague that we have provided interest-free loans to businesses. More than 669,000loans have been approved. We have continued to support businesses and Canadians during this time&#10;Speaker: The Chair&#10;Content: Mr.Deltell, you have time for a very brief question.&#10;Speaker: Mr. Grard Deltell&#10;Content: The only thing that distinguishes the provinces that table economic updates and the current government is political will. Why does Bill Morneau not have the political will to tell Canadians the truth?&#10;Speaker: Hon. Mona Fortier&#10;Content: Once again, we have been open and transparent. As soon as it is possible to provide clear economic projections, we will provide Canadians with a full update.&#10;Speaker: The Chair&#10;Content: We will now continue with Mr. Saroya.&#10;Speaker: Mr. Bob Saroya (MarkhamUnionville, CPC)&#10;Content: Thank you, Mr. Chair. CO" target="The question is asking why the Canadian federal government cannot provide an economic update during the uncertain times of COVID-19, when some provinces like Quebec, Saskatchewan, and Newfoundland have been able to do so.&#10;&#10;Minister Mona Fortier, the Canadian Finance Minister, has stated that the Canadian economy is going through a period of extraordinary uncertainty due to COVID-19 and that the government will continue to be open and transparent about the actions it is taking to support families, businesses, workers, and the healthcare system. However, she has not provided a clear economic projection yet. The opposition parties have criticized the government for not providing an economic update, arguing that Canadians deserve to know the state of the economy, especially given the current uncertainty caused by the pandemic.&#10;&#10;Minister Fortier has mentioned the implementation of the economic action plan to respond to COVID-19 and the provision of immediate assistance to Canadians, businesses, and workers. She has also highlighted the support provided through interest-free loans to businesses and continued support for businesses and Canadians during this time. However, she has not provided a clear answer regarding the reason for not providing an economic update.&#10;&#10;The opposition parties, including MPs Cathy McLeod, Grard Deltell, and John Williamson, have criticized the government for not providing an economic update, arguing that Canadians deserve to know the state of the economy, especially given the current uncertainty caused by the pandemic. They have pointed out that other provinces are able to provide updates on their economies while carrying out their responsibilities.&#10;&#10;In summary, the Canadian federal government has not provided a clear answer regarding why they cannot provide an economic update during these uncertain times, despite calls from opposition parties and some provinces doing so. The Finance Minister has emphasized the government's commitment to transparency and supporting Canadians but has not given a timeline for when an economic projection may be provided.">
