ctions it is taking to support families, businesses, workers, and the healthcare system. She also mentioned that the government reports biweekly to Parliament on the full cost and status of its economic measures, but has not provided a clear economic projection yet.&#10;&#10;On the other hand, opposition MPs Cathy McLeod and Grard Deltell have criticized the government for not providing an economic update, with McLeod pointing out that other governments have managed to provide updates for their citizens. They also argue that Canadians need to know the state of the economy, especially given the pre-existing economic troubles prior to COVID-19 and the current uncertainty caused by the pandemic.&#10;&#10;In summary, the government is facing pressure from the opposition parties to provide an economic update to Parliament and Canadians, but has not done so yet, citing the extraordinary uncertainty caused by COVID-19. The opposition parties argue that Canadians deserve to know the state of the economy and that the government's refusal to provide an update is a sign of a lack of transparency and accountability.">
